  "body": "Signed-off-by: Liqi Geng <gengliqiii@gmail.com>\r\n\r\n### What problem does this PR solve?\r\n\r\nIssue Number: close https://github.com/tikv/tikv/issues/8373\r\n\r\nProblem Summary:\r\n\r\nAfter https://github.com/tikv/tikv/pull/8301, it introduces a side effect when receiving an old snapshot.\r\nThis PR is to fix this issues.\r\nFor briefly, the snapshot may be rejected by raft-rs after checking snapshot in peer fsm. Thus some data change and behavior in `check_snapshot` have side effects. \r\nOne of the side effects is the remain data in `pending_snapshot_regions` which should be removed when this snapshot is rejected.\r\nSince `pending_snapshot_regions` can be changed only when holding a `StoreMeta` lock, we have two choices. One is checking raft-rs in `check_snapshot`, the other is removing it after the snapshot is rejected by raft-rs. Now I choose the latter.\r\n\r\nAnother issue is that the snapshot may not be used even all checking has passed. For example, a peer may receive a snapshot and then receive a stale-peer msg. If so, the data in `pending_snapshot_regions` should be removed during destroying the peer.\r\n\r\nAlso for the atomic snapshot(introduced by https://github.com/tikv/tikv/pull/8301), the flow is complicated and hard to interrupt. So I add a check to reject destroying when the atomic snapshot is ongoing.\r\n\r\n### What is changed and how it works?\r\n\r\nWhat's Changed:\r\ndescribed as above.\r\n\r\n### Related changes\r\n\r\n- Need to cherry-pick to the release branch\r\n\r\n### Check List <!--REMOVE the items that are not applicable-->\r\n\r\nTests <!-- At least one of them must be included. -->\r\n\r\n- Integration test\r\n\r\nSide effects\r\n\r\n- No.\r\n\r\n### Release note <!-- bugfixes or new feature need a release note -->\r\n\r\n* No release note",
